snippet.textDisplay:
I didn’t know what to expect when I saw she released this on Spotify the day it came out. I was walking home from work, and it became one of the most beautiful moments in my life.

I’ve struggled with substance abuse and living with multiple mental illnesses for my entire adult life. The last two drugs for me to overcome have been caffeine and nicotine. I recently let go of the cigarettes, and have been feeling amazing. A big part of my struggles have been largely based on self-worth issues.
The day this song was released was the first day I had felt amazing in a long time. Earlier on that day, the self-destructive thoughts started coming, making me doubt if I deserved to feel good, stable. But listening to this song on that walk home totally changed me. I got choked up, realizing that I do deserve it. That part in the chorus, “I see everything, I see everything,” hit me so hard. That night made this my favorite song.

Thank you, Grimes.

After reading the description it took me back when I was heavily addicted to xanax. I overdosed several times. Emergency rooms were common.

I never cried until listening this song. It made me think, what would have happened if I never woke up when I overdosed? My life would have ended at 20 years old. I guess it's a miracle that I pushed through and I've been clean for 14 years now.

Addiction is a lonely world.
